1
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:16,960
We need to check the letter?

2
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:21,960
Tomorrow begins a very special

3
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:23,960
limited-time "concept couple" date.

4
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:25,440
On the table, you'll find

5
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:27,080
three themed couple diaries:

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,800
Devotion, Passion, and New Beginnings.

7
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:31,720
This looks fun.

8
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:32,800
So it's not completely scripted.

9
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:34,760
Passion. The girl chases the guy.

10
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:36,680
(Passion)
There's even a storyline like that?

11
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:37,760
Devotion.

12
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:40,280
You're a couple in love for seven years

13
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,000
and planning to run away together.

14
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:44,240
New Beginnings

15
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:46,440
(First time calling him "hubby".)
You're newlyweds.

16
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:48,320
We're supposed to go on dates

17
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:49,120
following the diary.

18
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:50,080
But the rest of the story

19
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:51,920
hasn't been written yet.

20
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:52,760
Pretty interesting.

21
00:00:53,340 --> 00:00:57,580
=Episode 9 (Part 1)=
=Loving Journal=

22
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:00,200
Write the names of the chosen islanders

23
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,320
on the corresponding diaries.

24
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:03,260
(Passion)
(New Beginnings)

25
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:05,320
Let me think...

26
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:14,460
(Devotion)

27
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,000
That long?

28
00:01:16,440 --> 00:01:17,160
This is tough.

29
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,000
Is it really that hard?

30
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:18,800
Looks like three groups.

31
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:20,160
Three groups?

32
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,880
What's so hard about picking from three?

33
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:23,760
Which pair would pick us?

34
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:24,360
Which one though?

35
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,880
She'll definitely pick one for herself.

36
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:30,240
Then Jiayi's pair.

37
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:31,800
They might choose

38
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,080
Guanjie is...

39
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,360
Her roommate?

40
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:35,720
Yeah.

41
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:36,520
This is good.

42
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:37,840
I know how to do the groups.

43
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:41,720
Good.

44
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,360
Just because we're not her roommate.

45
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:50,840
All done?

46
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:52,960
Han.

47
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,320
Wait for the notice.

48
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:58,880
Why won't you look me in the eye?

49
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:01,560
Just wait for the notice.

50
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:04,280
See? You can't even look at me.

51
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:05,880
Look at Yan.

52
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,600
Come on, Wu Yihan.

53
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,680
The first day I met you,

54
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:16,040
you're like...

55
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:19,440
Attention, islanders.

56
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,720
Now announcing the islanders

57
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:22,960
heading out:

58
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:26,920
Liu Jiayi and Xuan Cheng.

59
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:31,240
(Passion)
This one's definitely Charlie.

60
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,040
Yeah.

61
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:32,760
Perfect.

62
00:02:35,220 --> 00:02:39,540
("Passion" - Xuan Cheng & Liu Jiayi)

63
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:43,240
Yang Tinghong and Zhao Enda.

64
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:47,420
(Only one date slot left.)

65
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,000
Seriously?

66
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:48,640
Bestie,

67
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:50,240
why didn't you plan one for me?

68
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,880
Zhu Huiyan and Wu Guanjie.

69
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,200
See?

70
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:02,800
Did she really not pick herself?

71
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:07,800
Why aren't you going out?

72
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,240
Cause we wanted you to have it.

73
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:10,840
What?

74
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,760
I'll bring you back food.

75
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,240
Nice.

76
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:12,960
Today we're...

77
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,080
Treating me like royalty?

78
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:14,920
Yeah, treating you like royalty.

79
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,080
Thanks.

80
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:17,840
Have fun.

81
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,640
Thanks.

82
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:20,600
Bestie.

83
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,440
Why are you doing this?

84
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:23,160
I think it's nice staying on the Island.

85
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:23,800
Cause after this...

86
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,520
Alright then...

87
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,080
Have fun staying.

88
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:25,520
Wait.

89
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,000
What's wrong? You gonna cry?

90
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:28,120
I'm a little touched.

91
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,560
You all go have fun.

92
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:30,840
We'll be fine here on the Island.

93
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,920
Yeah, I'll cook her something nice.

94
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:33,480
Right.

95
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,800
I don't want any of you to stay behind.

96
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,720
I'll bring you some food.

97
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:36,040
Sure.

98
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,120
I'll bring you loads of food.

99
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:39,800
Whoever got left out,

100
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,160
they might feel upset.

101
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,600
Better if we just happily

102
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,720
stay on the Island tomorrow.

103
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:44,120
Okay.

104
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:44,600
Right?

105
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:44,920
Alright.

106
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,600
We'll have a good time together.

107
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,080
Right?

108
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:47,640
Both agreed.

109
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:48,920
Alright.

110
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:50,720
Tomorrow I can make you...

111
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:51,880
Anyway, I'll cook for you.

112
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:52,280
Right?

113
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,440
Devotion is...

114
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,920
Yang's group?

115
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:56,840
Yeah, I think so.

116
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:57,120
Right?

117
00:03:59,020 --> 00:04:01,100
("Devotion" - Zhao Enda & Yang Tinghong)

118
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,760
So that leaves...

119
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:03,760
Yan and Guanjie.

120
00:04:04,740 --> 00:04:06,500
("New Beginnings"
- Wu Guanjie & Zhu Huiyan)

121
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,040
I'll bring you

122
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,160
a treat.

123
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,120
I felt really touched.

124
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:13,920
She didn't plan anything for herself.

125
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:14,720
But set it all up for us three.

126
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:15,520
Han is the kind of person

127
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:17,160
who wears her heart on her sleeve.

128
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,360
And when she cares about you,

129
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:20,400
she shows it through actions.

130
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,520
They lost the competition today.

131
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:23,960
Yan didn't even talk
to him the whole day.

132
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:24,800
Yeah.

133
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,400
Shouldn't you thank the two of us?

134
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:28,480
Thanks.

135
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,240
Is that how you say thanks?

136
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,160
Then what do you want me to do?

137
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:33,200
Bow down to our queen Han.

138
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:33,960
Want me to bow?

139
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:34,800
Bow to Queen Han.

140
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,240
Yan.

141
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,280
Feeling happy now.

142
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:39,000
I'm happy.

143
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:39,640
Happy.

144
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:40,520
Are you happy?

145
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,160
Happy.

146
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:43,360
Attention, islanders.

147
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,880
The 48-hour countdown for

148
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:47,320
Balance Island has begun.

149
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:55,900
(Balance Island countdown begins.)

150
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,600
Why they gotta do this...

151
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:00,080
Why...

152
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,360
48 hours left?

153
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:05,760
It's passing so fast.

154
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:06,800
Only 48 hours left.

155
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,480
I'll probably tell her

156
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,160
some of my

157
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,320
true feelings.

158
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,880
I've never confessed to a girl before,

159
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:16,800
so,

160
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,200
I'll need a bit of time for this,

161
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,680
like maybe forty-eight hours to prepare.

162
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,120
Too fast.

163
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,480
The countdown's already started.

164
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,360
Too fast.

165
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,240
I haven't even made up my mind,

166
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,040
and it's counting down.

167
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:27,840
What do I do?

168
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:35,920
Maybe because

169
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:38,920
I haven't really thought about

170
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,400
how things might end on this Island.

171
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,960
What kind of state I'll be in.

172
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,560
Honestly, I'm still

173
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,760
a little conflicted and hesitant.

174
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,200
48 hours is

175
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,160
a reasonable amount of time.

176
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,840
In two days, I think

177
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:53,040
Jiayi can also reach a good decision.

178
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,040
So fast.

179
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,640
I haven't even thought about it yet.

180
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,280
Are you happy

181
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:11,480
for the date?

182
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:11,960
Happy.

183
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,680
Seeing you already makes me happy.

184
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:14,400
Same here.

185
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,040
Have they all left?

186
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,320
Yeah, they've set off.

187
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,400
So it's just the five of us today?

188
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:32,080
Plus one.

189
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:32,520
Lu.

190
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,760
Lu.

191
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,120
Lu's still in his room.

192
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:35,920
Sad Lu.

193
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:48,360
It's me.

194
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:51,600
What's wrong?

195
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:52,320
Nothing.

196
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:52,920
Listen to me.

197
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,040
I'll cook for you later.

198
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,000
Really?

199
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,560
Really.

200
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,120
What's on the menu?

201
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,280
You like seafood, right?

202
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,200
Okay.

203
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:00,320
That's what this is about.

204
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:00,720
Yeah.

205
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:01,600
What else?

206
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:02,760
Alright then.

207
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:03,800
Should we

208
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,480
cook together?

209
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,360
We

210
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,000
six people?

211
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:06,640
Just the two of us.

212
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:07,840
Just us?

213
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,240
Right.

214
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:08,840
You're cooking for me.

215
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:10,680
Unless you want to invite them too.

216
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,200
Nope.

217
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,800
Making up for our agreement yesterday?

218
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,520
Still counts as a date.

219
00:07:14,780 --> 00:07:14,910
Okay.

220
00:07:14,910 --> 00:07:16,040
You really don't wanna date?

221
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:17,480
I didn't say that.

222
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:19,320
Not too eager either.

223
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:21,400
Go on.

224
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,120
Around 12.

225
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,800
I'll call you when it's ready.

226
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,680
Okay.

227
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,240
See you.

228
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:25,920
Do you need me to help?

229
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:26,400
Probably not?

230
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,160
What kind of help?

231
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:32,400
You literally lost that cake.

232
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:32,680
Alright.

233
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,520
Bye.

234
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:37,440
I knew it.

235
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:38,840
It was definitely meant for me.

236
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,280
Because I thought,

237
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:49,760
since she won that competition,

238
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:53,000
and decided to stay on the Island,

239
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,560
I should do something for her.

240
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:58,080
So I thought I'd make her dinner.

241
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,720
I made a shrimp broth

242
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,160
with rice noodles.

243
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,200
And

244
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,280
stir-fried clams with ginger and chili.

245
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:16,080
I just wanted to make up for not being

246
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,800
able to go out on the actual date today.

247
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:31,480
Coming.

248
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:33,480
Dinner's ready.

249
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:34,160
Really?

250
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:34,800
Yeah, really.

251
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:35,080
Let's go.

252
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:36,640
What were you doing?

253
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,240
Sleeping.

254
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:39,160
Seriously?

255
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:39,640
Yeah.

256
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,080
So happy.

257
00:08:41,740 --> 00:08:42,200
What did you make?

258
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,240
Waking up to a meal ready.

259
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:45,920
I made you Luosifen.

260
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:46,800
Really?

261
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:47,440
Yeah.

262
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,120
I don't believe you.

263
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:50,720
It's true.

264
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,360
I was gonna make pasta.

265
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,000
But then I thought

266
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,600
you like rice noodles more.

267
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,480
So I used shrimp

268
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,000
to make a broth.

269
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,080
Then added the Luosifen noodles.

270
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,120
I put in a lot of chili.

271
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:03,720
You know what?

272
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:04,760
It was so spicy even for me.

273
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,490
(From HK, China; From Sichuan)
You'd still think it's not spicy enough.

274
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:06,840
No way.

275
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:11,840
You actually made this?

276
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:12,120
Yeah.

277
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:13,920
Hold on for a sec.

278
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:16,640
You made this soup base?

279
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:17,760
Yeah.

280
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:18,680
You're really good at making soup.

281
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:20,800
I want to taste it.

282
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:25,400
It's hot.

283
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:35,080
Okay.

284
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,600
This is probably your limit for spicy.

285
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,000
Good.

286
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,000
It actually looks pretty nice.

287
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,440
The presentation is solid.

288
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,120
That Luosifen looks delicious.

289
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:43,480
It does.

290
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,400
Thanks.

291
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:46,920
It's nothing.

292
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,960
Seafood Luosifen.

293
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,080
Do you eat Luosifen often?

294
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,200
I love it.

295
00:09:59,200 --> 00:09:59,760
You?

296
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,080
We're crazy.

297
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,040
