But

1159
00:47:34,760 --> 00:47:35,960
living in the moment

1160
00:47:35,960 --> 00:47:36,840
was your idea too.

1161
00:47:37,480 --> 00:47:38,280
Having a pure,

1162
00:47:39,320 --> 00:47:39,880
real relationship

1163
00:47:39,880 --> 00:47:40,680
was also your idea.

1164
00:47:46,640 --> 00:47:48,560
That notebook helped me

1165
00:47:49,680 --> 00:47:51,360
find what I really feel.

1166
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:00,920
I think many challenges in real life

1167
00:48:01,600 --> 00:48:05,840
are unpredictable,

1168
00:48:06,240 --> 00:48:07,280
like long-distance,

1169
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:09,160
or things you never see coming.

1170
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:15,040
But I think those challenges,

1171
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:17,040
compared to,

1172
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:19,280
compared to losing you,

1173
00:48:19,280 --> 00:48:20,240
none of them means anything.

1174
00:48:25,440 --> 00:48:27,200
Then what's the point of us coming here?

1175
00:48:27,680 --> 00:48:28,480
Are you even listening to me?

1176
00:48:30,080 --> 00:48:31,320
I said, compared to losing you,

1177
00:48:32,720 --> 00:48:33,640
none of those challenges

1178
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:36,080
means anything.

1179
00:48:40,200 --> 00:48:40,920
So,

1180
00:48:44,640 --> 00:48:46,440
that wasn't your real answer?

1181
00:48:47,280 --> 00:48:48,280
It was the notebook.

1182
00:48:51,840 --> 00:48:52,920
When I read it,

1183
00:48:53,280 --> 00:48:55,160
I couldn't believe the last few lines.

1184
00:48:55,510 --> 00:48:58,160
(You've decided to let go of what was.)
To give this dying relationship an end.

1185
00:48:58,160 --> 00:48:59,400
So after the fireworks died out,

1186
00:48:59,400 --> 00:49:00,170
you want to say,

1187
00:49:00,170 --> 00:49:01,130
let's break up.

1188
00:49:01,130 --> 00:49:01,720
Let's break up.

1189
00:49:01,720 --> 00:49:02,780
(Turns and leaves without looking back)

1190
00:49:04,520 --> 00:49:05,600
I thought I misread it,

1191
00:49:05,600 --> 00:49:07,120
so I checked it again.

1192
00:49:07,120 --> 00:49:08,360
I saw that he'd already finished reading,

1193
00:49:08,360 --> 00:49:09,600
but I was still reading.

1194
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:11,720
I was like,

1195
00:49:12,560 --> 00:49:13,720
what does this mean?

1196
00:49:13,720 --> 00:49:14,920
It's like a bolt out of the blue.

1197
00:49:15,440 --> 00:49:16,880
The words are so hurtful.

1198
00:49:17,500 --> 00:49:18,980
(On the drive back to Balance Island)
My heart's breaking.

1199
00:49:18,980 --> 00:49:19,520
What was I thinking?

1200
00:49:19,520 --> 00:49:20,920
Just to follow the script,

1201
00:49:20,920 --> 00:49:21,880
I had to say those words.

1202
00:49:21,880 --> 00:49:22,320
But I

1203
00:49:22,840 --> 00:49:23,720
really couldn't say it.

1204
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:24,520
When I saw his face,

1205
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:25,400
his sincere,

1206
00:49:26,480 --> 00:49:27,520
earnest look,

1207
00:49:27,520 --> 00:49:28,720
his eyes,

1208
00:49:28,720 --> 00:49:30,200
I just couldn't get the words out.

1209
00:49:30,200 --> 00:49:32,200
Losing once doesn't mean
I'll lose forever.

1210
00:49:32,200 --> 00:49:33,920
I don't always lose at games.

1211
00:49:33,920 --> 00:49:34,880
I must win.

1212
00:49:34,880 --> 00:49:35,760
I'll win eventually.

1213
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:36,640
I've already forgotten it.

1214
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:37,320
I want to try again.

1215
00:49:38,840 --> 00:49:40,720
I didn't dare look into his eyes.

1216
00:49:41,720 --> 00:49:42,640
I steeled myself,

1217
00:49:42,640 --> 00:49:43,680
looked away from his face,

1218
00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:44,440
and said those words.

1219
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:46,400
(On the drive back to Balance Island)

1220
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:48,440
Then I ran off, and he came after me.

1221
00:49:49,320 --> 00:49:50,000
When he caught up,

1222
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,480
he grabbed my wrist tightly,

1223
00:49:51,480 --> 00:49:52,520
but not enough

1224
00:49:53,520 --> 00:49:54,560
to hurt me.

1225
00:49:55,440 --> 00:49:56,720
Still, he held on really tight.

1226
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:00,680
It's much harder than real challenges.

1227
00:50:02,480 --> 00:50:04,000
I can't bear to break up with him.

1228
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:11,960
I thought it was

1229
00:50:13,400 --> 00:50:14,480
your own answer.

1230
00:50:15,400 --> 00:50:15,920
Scared?

1231
00:50:18,120 --> 00:50:19,160
Unbelievable.

1232
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:23,040
So what did it say on your note?

1233
00:50:23,560 --> 00:50:24,040
Did it say...

1234
00:50:24,040 --> 00:50:24,760
Let's break up.

1235
00:50:29,160 --> 00:50:30,120
What did yours say?

1236
00:50:30,880 --> 00:50:32,040
Let's keep going.

1237
00:50:32,960 --> 00:50:34,160
Yeah. So you were

1238
00:50:34,160 --> 00:50:36,760
acting your script, weren't you?

1239
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:37,520
I don't need to act.

1240
00:50:37,520 --> 00:50:39,000
I want us to keep going.

1241
00:50:39,000 --> 00:50:39,880
I had to act!

1242
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:40,960
I never wanted to break up.

1243
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:49,320
Acting it was killing me.

1244
00:50:59,640 --> 00:51:00,440
Can you change your shoes now?

1245
00:51:01,680 --> 00:51:01,960
Let's go.

1246
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:03,520
Not now.

1247
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:04,400
Let's go to the living room first.

1248
00:51:05,800 --> 00:51:06,680
A roller-coaster of emotions.

1249
00:51:07,320 --> 00:51:08,280
I'm happy, of course,

1250
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:08,760
like

1251
00:51:09,680 --> 00:51:11,000
flowers suddenly blooming,

1252
00:51:12,200 --> 00:51:13,440
like the sun coming out after rain.

1253
00:51:14,200 --> 00:51:14,840
What happened?

1254
00:51:15,600 --> 00:51:15,960
You're back.

1255
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:17,760
Today's date felt like a prank,

1256
00:51:17,760 --> 00:51:18,360
you know?

1257
00:51:18,740 --> 00:51:19,200
It's all good now?

1258
00:51:19,200 --> 00:51:20,320
Your date was crazy, right?

1259
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:21,480
We got a diary

1260
00:51:21,480 --> 00:51:22,800
and had to immerse ourselves

1261
00:51:22,800 --> 00:51:24,960
in acting whatever it said.

1262
00:51:24,960 --> 00:51:25,920
So you were just acting earlier?

1263
00:51:26,360 --> 00:51:27,440
The last line said we...

1264
00:51:27,440 --> 00:51:28,920
So I thought her decision

1265
00:51:28,920 --> 00:51:30,000
was real.

1266
00:51:32,240 --> 00:51:34,280
They were both acting!

1267
00:51:34,340 --> 00:51:37,020
(Look what we've done.)

1268
00:51:37,320 --> 00:51:38,760
(Hits hard)
And I had to say it out loud,

1269
00:51:38,760 --> 00:51:40,400
then run away right after.

1270
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:42,400
So you rejected him to his face?

1271
00:51:42,400 --> 00:51:42,800
Yeah.

1272
00:51:43,360 --> 00:51:43,760
Bro,

1273
00:51:44,160 --> 00:51:45,080
if it were me,

1274
00:51:45,080 --> 00:51:46,920
(Listen to Lu)
I'd pull my car right in front of them.

1275
00:51:46,920 --> 00:51:48,520
(Listen to Lu, can't go wrong)
I'd block them.

1276
00:51:48,520 --> 00:51:49,520
I'd be right behind,

1277
00:51:49,520 --> 00:51:49,920
you know,

1278
00:51:49,920 --> 00:51:51,240
(No empty talk)
flashing my lights like crazy.

1279
00:51:52,680 --> 00:51:53,640
You're that type?

1280
00:51:54,120 --> 00:51:54,740
I wouldn't have guessed.

1281
00:51:55,120 --> 00:51:56,680
I thought you'd just silently cry

1282
00:51:56,680 --> 00:51:58,080
and then slip away.

1283
00:51:58,680 --> 00:51:59,120
Nah.

1284
00:52:00,080 --> 00:52:01,720
It's ok. Singapore's ok.

1285
00:52:02,120 --> 00:52:03,840
I said my solution is

1286
00:52:03,840 --> 00:52:05,840
to move to her city

1287
00:52:05,840 --> 00:52:06,640
and live there for a month.

1288
00:52:07,580 --> 00:52:08,480
(Is this what love is?)

1289
00:52:08,480 --> 00:52:09,760
Good, good.

1290
00:52:10,120 --> 00:52:11,600
Enda's idea is actually good.

1291
00:52:11,600 --> 00:52:11,960
Good.

1292
00:52:12,360 --> 00:52:13,200
Get settled first.

1293
00:52:13,800 --> 00:52:15,040
Long-term plan is

1294
00:52:15,040 --> 00:52:16,280
I switch jobs.

1295
00:52:16,920 --> 00:52:18,800
I think I can work remotely.

1296
00:52:18,800 --> 00:52:20,000
Live-stream sales.

1297
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:21,400
Three, two, one, drop the link.

1298
00:52:22,600 --> 00:52:24,120
Can you not make it sound so low?

1299
00:52:24,120 --> 00:52:25,480
How can you make it sound so low?

1300
00:52:25,480 --> 00:52:27,080
No, I was just giving an example.

1301
00:52:27,080 --> 00:52:28,080
You do backend control?

1302
00:52:28,480 --> 00:52:29,960
No. How is that possible?

1303
00:52:31,360 --> 00:52:33,000
No, I will.

1304
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:34,400
I'll do backend control.

1305
00:52:35,000 --> 00:52:36,600
We meant well, but it backfired.

1306
00:52:37,120 --> 00:52:38,400
Still, we're lucky.

1307
00:52:39,100 --> 00:52:40,040
(That's me, the unlucky one.)

1308
00:52:40,040 --> 00:52:41,280
I think the other two dates are tough too.

1309
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:43,040
Bet they all

1310
00:52:43,040 --> 00:52:43,880
had tasks assigned.

1311
00:52:43,880 --> 00:52:45,120
I hope they're ok.

1312
00:52:45,800 --> 00:52:46,200
Me too.

1313
00:52:47,600 --> 00:52:49,160
I can't wait for them to come back.

1314
00:52:49,520 --> 00:52:51,120
I hope they come back happy.

1315
00:52:51,760 --> 00:52:53,080
That would mean my plan worked.

1316
00:52:53,560 --> 00:52:55,960
If our plan breaks up three couples,

1317
00:52:55,960 --> 00:52:56,880
we'd really...

1318
00:52:57,040 --> 00:52:57,840
Anyway, it's all good now.

1319
00:52:57,840 --> 00:52:58,300
Yeah.

1320
00:52:58,300 --> 00:52:59,040
Fortunately, it's all good.

1321
00:52:59,040 --> 00:53:00,400
They are more stable now.

1322
00:53:01,560 --> 00:53:02,560
Wanna go change your shoes?

1323
00:53:03,600 --> 00:53:04,080
I'll go with you.

1324
00:53:04,760 --> 00:53:05,720
Let's take care of it.

1325
00:53:05,720 --> 00:53:06,600
Alright, I'll change them.

1326
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:07,240
I'll come with you.

1327
00:53:07,240 --> 00:53:08,040
Go change your shoes.

1328
00:53:08,400 --> 00:53:09,360
Yeah.

1329
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:10,080
Go ahead.

1330
00:53:10,080 --> 00:53:10,760
Go.

1331
00:53:15,520 --> 00:53:16,920
Are you crazy, Lu Yanting?

1332
00:53:16,920 --> 00:53:17,960
Why did you drink so much?

1333
00:53:18,280 --> 00:53:20,160
No, I was never crazy.

1334
00:53:20,160 --> 00:53:21,120
But I am now.

1335
00:53:22,640 --> 00:53:23,480
He's upset.

1336
00:53:24,800 --> 00:53:26,240
(A heartbroken boy)
We'll hang out with you,

1337
00:53:26,240 --> 00:53:27,240
ok? If you're upset.

1338
00:53:27,400 --> 00:53:28,600
You're dating, ok?

1339
00:53:30,200 --> 00:53:30,880
Even if I weren't,

1340
00:53:30,880 --> 00:53:32,000
I wouldn't be like him.

1341
00:53:32,600 --> 00:53:34,440
I get it. It's ok.

1342
00:53:34,440 --> 00:53:35,440
When she comes back,

1343
00:53:35,440 --> 00:53:36,680
I'm gonna tell her straight up

1344
00:53:36,680 --> 00:53:38,400
that I'll give her everything I have.

1345
00:53:39,920 --> 00:53:41,200
(Surprisingly generous)
Everything I have.

1346
00:53:43,510 --> 00:53:44,550
All of it.

1347
00:53:44,680 --> 00:53:45,240
I think

1348
00:53:46,160 --> 00:53:47,480
if they come back ok,

1349
00:53:47,480 --> 00:53:48,640
maybe we don't say anything.

1350
00:53:48,640 --> 00:53:49,200
I'm gonna say it.

1351
00:53:52,840 --> 00:53:53,680
I think

1352
00:53:53,680 --> 00:53:55,120
(Here's some real talk)
speaking your mind is ok.

1353
00:53:55,560 --> 00:53:56,120
But...

1354
00:53:56,440 --> 00:53:57,920
You should consider Xuan's feelings

1355
00:53:57,920 --> 00:53:58,960
and make sure he's comfortable.

1356
00:53:59,400 --> 00:54:01,080
If he's not, it's not good.

1357
00:54:01,480 --> 00:54:02,680
No, if they come back ok,

1358
00:54:02,680 --> 00:54:03,280
I'll still say it.

1359
00:54:03,380 --> 00:54:04,340
(I must feel comfortable)

1360
00:54:04,760 --> 00:54:05,760
(Who dares to stop me?)
Who's stopping me?

1361
00:54:05,760 --> 00:54:06,240
I am.

1362
00:54:06,240 --> 00:54:07,000
(Love security)

1363
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:08,080
(How are you gonna stop me?)
You can't stop me.

1364
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:08,940
(Try me.)
I'll definitely stop you.

1365
00:54:09,680 --> 00:54:10,480
No need.

1366
00:54:10,480 --> 00:54:11,640
I'm just being myself,

1367
00:54:11,640 --> 00:54:12,720
speaking my mind.

1368
00:54:13,960 --> 00:54:14,640
No regrets,

1369
00:54:14,640 --> 00:54:15,040
you know?

1370
00:54:15,040 --> 00:54:16,760
I hate having regrets.

1371
00:54:17,280 --> 00:54:18,560
I'll regret it if I don't do this.

1372
00:54:21,220 --> 00:54:22,200
(Time to run)
Wanna go talk?

1373
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:22,760
Sure.

1374
00:54:22,760 --> 00:54:23,360
Love to death.

1375
00:54:23,360 --> 00:54:24,240
These two are crazy in love.

1376
00:54:24,540 --> 00:54:26,700
(Can't reason with him. Can't stop him.)

1377
00:54:31,360 --> 00:54:32,680
Don't act like a kid,

1378
00:54:32,680 --> 00:54:33,200
I'm telling you.

1379
00:54:33,560 --> 00:54:34,520
Be mature.

1380
00:54:34,520 --> 00:54:35,240
I'm immature.

1381
00:54:35,880 --> 00:54:36,840
I'm just an immature guy.

1382
00:54:36,840 --> 00:54:38,880
But what's the point?

1383
00:54:38,880 --> 00:54:40,560
You know she's already made her choice.

1384
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:41,840
Why do you have to tell her

1385
00:54:41,840 --> 00:54:43,480
you'll give her everything?

1386
00:54:43,480 --> 00:54:44,000
Why bother?

1387
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:45,880
I want to express myself.

1388
00:54:45,880 --> 00:54:46,680
Do you have to

1389
00:54:46,680 --> 00:54:47,720
do something

1390
00:54:47,720 --> 00:54:48,480
so undignified

1391
00:54:48,480 --> 00:54:49,480
for a man?

1392
00:54:49,840 --> 00:54:50,560
I don't care about dignity.

1393
00:54:51,840 --> 00:54:52,760
I know who I am.

1394
00:54:52,760 --> 00:54:53,400
I don't get it.

1395
00:54:54,160 --> 00:54:54,960
I just don't.

1396
00:54:54,960 --> 00:54:56,360
If Xuan tries to stop you,

1397
00:54:56,360 --> 00:54:57,200
are you gonna punch him?

1398
00:54:57,680 --> 00:54:58,320
Would he stop me?

1399
00:55:00,120 --> 00:55:01,040
If it were me,

1400
00:55:01,040 --> 00:55:02,080
who do you think you are to say that?

1401
00:55:02,080 --> 00:55:04,160
A guy says I'll give you everything.

1402
00:55:04,160 --> 00:55:04,920
What would you think?

1403
00:55:04,920 --> 00:55:05,720
Come on.

1404
00:55:05,720 --> 00:55:06,620
(Bring it on!)
Say it!

1405
00:55:07,080 --> 00:55:07,880
I don't care.

1406
00:55:09,040 --> 00:55:09,800
Suit yourself.

1407
00:55:09,800 --> 00:55:11,300
(Can't stop him, just avoid him.)

1408
00:55:18,000 --> 00:55:18,720
Are you hot?

1409
00:55:19,760 --> 00:55:20,160
No.

1410
00:55:20,640 --> 00:55:22,040
Have some water.

1411
00:55:22,040 --> 00:55:22,680
I'm fine.

1412
00:55:23,240 --> 00:55:24,480
Do you think I care about my image?

1413
00:55:24,480 --> 00:55:25,040
I don't.

1414
00:55:26,560 --> 00:55:28,360
We'll leave first.

1415
00:55:28,360 --> 00:55:30,860
(Nothing else)
(Just peace out)

1416
00:55:32,540 --> 00:55:35,060
(Love is a wine that gets everyone drunk)

1417
00:55:37,840 --> 00:55:38,480
Come.

1418
00:55:38,480 --> 00:55:39,520
Only two chairs.

1419
00:55:39,520 --> 00:55:40,840
Let's put them together.

1420
00:55:40,840 --> 00:55:41,480
Ok.

1421
00:55:45,360 --> 00:55:45,960
I'll sit here.

1422
00:55:46,680 --> 00:55:47,440
He's drunk.

1423
00:55:48,240 --> 00:55:49,360
Can someone love that much?

1424
00:55:49,920 --> 00:55:50,360
Honestly,

1425
00:55:50,360 --> 00:55:51,480
if he did that for me,

1426
00:55:51,480 --> 00:55:52,360
I'd be touched.

1427
00:55:53,040 --> 00:55:53,280
Me too.

1428
00:55:53,280 --> 00:55:55,160
If I wasn't interested in him at all,

1429
00:55:55,160 --> 00:55:55,780
it wouldn't work.

1430
00:55:55,880 --> 00:55:57,080
But if I was even a little interested,

1431
00:55:57,080 --> 00:55:58,360
I'd see it as a plus.

1432
00:55:58,360 --> 00:56:00,440
But he should've did this from the start.

1433
00:56:00,880 --> 00:56:02,360
But I also feel that his affection

1434
00:56:02,360 --> 00:56:03,280
is a bit

1435
00:56:03,280 --> 00:56:03,680
overwhelming

1436
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:04,160
and intense.

1437
00:56:04,480 --> 00:56:05,080
A bit overwhelming.

1438
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:07,040
But he hates regrets,

1439
00:56:07,040 --> 00:56:07,920
so he...

1440
